{"title": "Streaming changes: Evolutionary, bold but not far enough", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2019-03-10", "content": "On Tuesday, Education Minister Ong Ye Kung told Singaporeans that from 2024, streaming will be replaced with a system that lets students study subjects at different levels instead of the levels they were streamed into. He was careful not to use the word scrap, abolish or end.\nBut the effect of the changes is that streaming as Singaporeans have understood it for four decades will end."}